This paper presents an empirical study of behavioral service profiles collected from millions of users whose devices are deployed with Wandoujia, a leading Android app-store service in China. The study explores multiple aspects of such behavioral data and presents patterns of app usage. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), followed by cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.SE (Software Engineering), and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
